---
import FeaturePageLayout from "../../layouts/FeaturePageLayout.astro";
import DownloadButton from "../../components/button/DownloadButton";
import DownloadMuseHubButton from "../../components/button/DownloadMuseHubButton";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import AudacityMockUp from "../../assets/img/HeroBannerImage.webp";
import Shortcut from "../../components/Shortcut.astro";
---

<FeaturePageLayout
  title="Copy Audio – Copy Selection to Clipboard | Audacity"
  description="Copy selected audio to the clipboard without removing it. Reuse sections, move audio between tracks, back up before editing. Free for Windows, Mac & Linux."
  canonical="https://www.audacityteam.org/features/copy/"
>
  <Fragment slot="hero">
    <section id="main" class="bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-900 to-blue-700">
      <div class="mx-auto px-4 md:px-8 py-4 md:py-8 lg:py-12 max-w-screen-lg">
        <div
          class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between gap-8 md:gap-12"
        >
          <div class="flex flex-col text-center md:text-left md:w-1/2 gap-6">
            <h1
              class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-semibold text-white leading-tight"
            >
              Copy Audio in Audacity &ndash; Send Any Selection to the Clipboard
            </h1>
            <p class="text-white text-lg opacity-90">
              Copy any selection without removing the original, then paste it
              anywhere in the same track, another track, or another project.
            </p>
            <div
              class="flex flex-col w-full md:w-fit gap-4 items-center md:items-start pb-2"
            >
              <DownloadMuseHubButton client:load />
              <noscript><DownloadMuseHubButton client:load /></noscript>
              <DownloadButton client:load />
              <noscript><DownloadButton client:load /></noscript>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="hidden md:block md:w-1/2">
            <Image
              src={AudacityMockUp}
              alt="A laptop showing the Audacity application"
              width={668}
              quality={80}
              loading="eager"
              class="w-full h-auto"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </Fragment>

  <div class="not-prose my-8 rounded-lg border border-blue-200 bg-blue-50 p-6">
    <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900">
      Copy audio in 4 steps:
    </h3>
    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-blue-800">
      <li>Select the waveform range you want to copy</li>
      <li>
        Press <Shortcut keys="Ctrl+C" /> (or Cmd+C on Mac), or use Edit &gt; Copy
      </li>
      <li>Move to your destination point</li>
      <li>Paste with <Shortcut keys="Ctrl+V" /> / Cmd+V</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <h2>What Is the Copy Command?</h2>
  <p>
    Copy sends selected audio to Audacity's clipboard while leaving the source
    unchanged. It is a non-destructive way to duplicate phrases, back up
    sections before processing, and move content between tracks or projects.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Copy Audio in Audacity</h2>
  <h3>Step 1: Select the Audio You Want to Copy</h3>
  <p>
    Click and drag across the target region. For whole-track copy, use <Shortcut
      keys="Ctrl+A"
    /> first.
  </p>

  <h3>Step 2: Apply the Copy Command (Ctrl+C / Cmd+C)</h3>
  <p>Run Copy from keyboard or Edit menu.</p>

  <h3>Step 3: Move the Cursor to the Paste Point</h3>
  <p>
    Click destination location in the same track or another compatible
    track/project.
  </p>

  <h3>Step 4: Paste with Ctrl+V / Cmd+V</h3>
  <p>Paste inserts or replaces depending on destination selection state.</p>

  <h2>Copy Command Behavior Explained</h2>
  <h3>Keyboard Shortcut (Ctrl+C / Cmd+C)</h3>
  <p>Copy executes instantly with no dialog.</p>

  <h3>Audacity Clipboard</h3>
  <p>
    Audacity keeps the most recent copied/cut item until it is replaced or the
    app closes.
  </p>

  <h3>Non-Destructive by Design</h3>
  <p>
    Copy never removes source audio, making it safer than cut when you are
    experimenting.
  </p>

  <h3>Copy Between Tracks and Projects</h3>
  <p>
    You can paste copied material across tracks and across open projects,
    subject to compatibility rules.
  </p>

  <h3>Mono and Stereo Rules</h3>
  <p>
    Mono can paste into stereo tracks; stereo cannot paste into mono tracks.
    Track types must match.
  </p>

  <h2>Copy vs Cut vs Duplicate</h2>
  <div
    class="not-prose my-8 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50"
  >
    <table class="w-full text-sm text-left">
      <thead>
        <tr class="bg-gray-100">
          <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-gray-900">Command</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-gray-900"
            >Source After Command</th
          >
          <th class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-gray-900">Clipboard Used</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200 text-gray-700">
        <tr
          ><td class="px-4 py-3">Copy</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Unchanged</td
          ><td class="px-4 py-3">Yes</td></tr
        >
        <tr
          ><td class="px-4 py-3">Cut</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Removed</td><td
            class="px-4 py-3">Yes</td
          ></tr
        >
        <tr
          ><td class="px-4 py-3">Duplicate</td><td class="px-4 py-3"
            >Unchanged + copy created</td
          ><td class="px-4 py-3">No</td></tr
        >
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Common Use Cases</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Duplicate choruses and repeated phrases</li>
    <li>Back up a region before destructive processing</li>
    <li>Move source material between tracks/projects</li>
    <li>Build loops from short phrases</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips for Best Results</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Use clear selection boundaries to avoid partial transient cuts.</li>
    <li>Name clips/tracks before complex copy-paste sessions.</li>
    <li>Combine copy with snap/grid settings for tempo-accurate edits.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Does Copy remove original audio?</strong><br />No, Copy is
    non-destructive.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Can I paste copied audio multiple times?</strong><br />Yes, until
    clipboard content is replaced.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Can Copy move between projects?</strong><br />Yes, between open
    projects if types/channels are compatible.
  </p>

  <h2>Download Audacity Free</h2>
  <p>
    Download Audacity on Windows, macOS, and Linux to copy and arrange audio
    quickly.
  </p>
  <div
    class="not-prose mt-8 flex flex-col w-full md:w-fit gap-4 items-center sm:items-start text-left"
  >
    <DownloadMuseHubButton client:load />
    <noscript><DownloadMuseHubButton client:load /></noscript>
    <DownloadButton client:load />
    <noscript><DownloadButton client:load /></noscript>
  </div>
</FeaturePageLayout>
